text:
Follow us Bayern Munich’s Mats Hummels expects ‘world-class’ Mesut Ozil to start for Arsenal in Champions League clash Louis Sealey for Metro.co.uk Tuesday 14 Feb 2017 10:20 pm Mesut Ozil has struggled for Arsenal recently and could be dropped (Picture: Getty) 
Mats Hummels expects ‘world-class’ Mesut Ozil to start for Arsenal in the Champions League against Bayern Munich on Wednesday. 
Ozil could be dropped by Gunners boss Arsene Wenger after a string of below-par performances in the Premier League. 
Wenger has refused to be drawn on whether Ozil will start for his side, stating: ‘It’s not the best moment to give out the XI. 
‘I will pick the team tomorrow.’ 
Despite his recent struggles, Ozil has been labelled as ‘world-class’ by Hummels, who insists he expects his compatriot to start at the Allianz Arena. 
‘For me it was a surprise that Mesut is doubtful to play,’ the Bayern defender said. Mats Hummels expects Ozil to start for Arsenal (Picture: Getty) 
‘He is a world-class player and someone who is always put on the field. I think he will be on the pitch tomorrow from the first minute because he is a class player.
